      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        javax.xml.stream.XMLStreamException,
                        SBMLException
        Reads the file that is passed as argument and write it to the console, using the method SBMLWriter.write(SBMLDocument, java.io.OutputStream).
        Parameters:
        args - the command line arguments, we are taking the first one as the file name to read.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the file name is not valid.
        SBMLException - if there are any problems reading or writing the SBML model.
        javax.xml.stream.XMLStreamException - if there are any problems reading or writing the XML file.

      • readXMLFromXMLEventReader

        private java.lang.Object readXMLFromXMLEventReader(javax.xml.stream.XMLEventReader xmlEventReader,
                                         TreeNodeChangeListener listener)
                                            throws javax.xml.stream.XMLStreamException
        Reads an XML document from the given XMLEventReader. It need to represent a self contain part of an SBML document. It can be either a math element, a notes element or the whole SBML model. If math or notes are given, a Rule containing the math or notes will be returned, otherwise an SBMLDocument is returned.
        Parameters:
        xmlEventReader -
        listener -
        Returns:
        an Object representing the given XML.
        Throws:
        javax.xml.stream.XMLStreamException
